column9: g'day
or should i say, g'day
Oh, hey, how are things in aussieland?
hopefully ok, i haven't gone outside yet...
still got good weather over there?
Uh, its raining, but yeah. BTW, I was happy because summer is over, not here ;)
Summer is so hot and humid here you can't move
yeah, you guys get it tough over there
am looking at Heppbury-Brentham trains
we need more of them, i just added 2
Yeah. Please use high speed trains (not sd40
we will end up with congestion of these trains at Brentham, i'm sure
oh, ok, i'll replace the sd40's
sd40s are good only on 120 kmh lines, where i've got higher speeds let's use
'em
Brentham should be fine, I spent a long time untangling it this afternoon
of course, i'm not familiar with the vehicles in this pakset so am trying to follow you
I had to undo most of your work there.
i noticed! my work was only a patch job
Well, I took at least an hour to redo it, It's good for the next million ton-miles ;)
i'll have 3 spare sd40's if you want them sent to any particular depots
just send 'em wherever. Maybe put a sign so we know we have stabled power?
i find them using a filtered search
you've probably seen my depot routes for sending them to the depots i want
it's also fun seeing light engines running around the map
Yeah, I try really hard not to delete useful convoys, Instead sending them around...
like the switchers at 234, 121
press details and you'll see there 1957 power

hang on, just replacing the sd40s
do we have any spare brose234's?
Not that I know of.
the 218's are the same speed anyway
No, use 234
oh, ok, i'll bring in an existing consist and duplicate
?? 234s are still in productions
*production
of course, i'm just blind
i thought we were using sd40's to get the extra mail car on
I did some calculations, and I think I found that it is more profitable to use a 234 at 139 kmh with 6 cars than an sd40-2 with 7 at 119 kmh
You know about the speedbonus change, right?
Of course, still better to use an sd40-2 where track speed is only 120kmh
Oh, that's a nice jam
i don't take $ quite seriously enough to do speedbonus calculations
or even bother to understand how it works
I don't *really* care, but I just love doing the math sometimes...
fair enough, i haven't got that bored yet :)
But the change is now that speedbonus is based on actual maximum speed, not theoretical
excellent, that's a step in the right direction
So, a 234 will make less money running on a 120kmh track than an sd40, but the opposite is true on higher speed track
towards calculating it on average speed
So, it gives a little more strategy to convoy creation
indeed. did you say we have a jam somewhere?
Fixed already :)
More of my shoddy signaling
That has gone unnoticed since 1960...
it probably didn't matter until the line got busy
Isn't that the truth,
By the way, the jam at Appingchester steel mill that you mentioned to me was not an issue of signaling, but seemed to be a bug of some sort
The presignal did not trigger the choose signal and treated it like a normal signal
I will investigate in a nightly to see if I can repeat the behavior
i didn't look at the signalling, i just found a short-term fix and figured i'd leave the proper fix to you
Oh, yeah, you got the quick patch right on. Just sometimes, like at brentham, there is not easy patch because it is so convoluted an interchange
yes, and i don't know where all the trains are going
i had to do something because it was jammed to a stop
Right now it is a four-level stack interchange! But it began in 1935ish as a terminus if you can imagine...
And I just kept adding and other people's lines got in my way more and more
yes, i looked
i'm wating for the function where the player with the most money can dynamite others' infrastructure...
Yeah! i can drop a cool 30 billion on that!
Hell, I could buy out every other player on the map!
getting to the $1m a day target is proving a challenge, i must say
mmm, buying out players
Oh, but we're in shooting distance, only 25 million off...
should i get a mail network happening on the northern edge?
Before that: @177273
ok
A new station & line are at the ready, I think maybe use that instead of trucking all the way to Mailiton

good. i add trucks as i find lines that need them

good. i'll try to leave new rail line construction to you as you have the master plan in your head and i don't

sure, i just want to make sure i don't load up lines that may already be at capacity
And master plan calls for a new wood line in the same areas....
At the very least, i need new junctions.
Ok, where are the nearest sd40s to Oakstead?
probably 416,274
i've got to go, catch you later
Bye!
